According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Smart Home Market was valued at USD 32.8 billion in 2025 and is projected to grow from USD 35.6 billion in 2026 to USD 58.9 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 6.1% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing robust growth due to rising consumer demand for energy-efficient homes, increasing adoption of IoT-enabled devices, and expanding deployment of smart security, lighting, and climate control systems across Europe. Government initiatives promoting energy conservation, coupled with advancements in wireless connectivity and AI-powered home automation, continue to strengthen market expansion.
